          "The Musk-driven Twitter drama is only just getting going, it seems."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "And this morning I wake up to this news:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "blockquote",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Members of Twitter‚Äôs Trust and Safety Council received an email with the subject line, ‚ÄúThank You,‚Äù that informed them the council was no longer ‚Äúthe best structure‚Äù to bring ‚Äúexternal insights into our product and policy development work.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Yes, Musk has "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            1
          ],
          1,
          "disbanded Twitter‚Äôs Trust and Safety Council"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ". Here‚Äôs the full message they received:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      0
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h2",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The great Twitter dictator"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "It really does look like Musk‚Äôs ruling Twitter by diktat. It‚Äôs only six weeks since Musk said this:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      1
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "And yet, he‚Äôs been reinstating people willy-nilly, and using Twitter polls to make decisions. Given that he‚Äôs disbanded one of the most prominent external advisory boards, how likely is it he will actually even convene that decision-making committee?"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "At least some council members could see the writing on the wall, and quit a few days ago:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      2
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h2",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Closing himself to contrary opinions"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Musk isn‚Äôt one for seeking contrary opinions, or at least "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          0,
          "so suggested council member Larry Magid to the "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            3
          ],
          2,
          "Washington Post"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ":"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "blockquote",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúBy disbanding it, we got fired instead of quit,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúElon doesn‚Äôt want criticism, and he really doesn‚Äôt want the kind of advice he would very likely get from a safety advisory council, which would likely tell him to rehire some of the staff he got rid of, and reinstate some of the rules he got rid of, and turn the company in another direction from where he is turning it.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Historically, Twitter has been perceived as an unfocused company with wooly leadership. Those days are clearly over. It‚Äôs now the plaything of a highly opinionated billionaire. And the only opinion he‚Äôs really considering is his own."
        ]
      ]
